description: Beef poultry farms are the farms where cows are raised for beef production.
It is a poultry farm where a broiler chicken is bred and raised specifically for meat production
Layer poultry farming means raising egg laying poultry birds for the purpose of commercial egg production
It is the raising and breeding of domestic sheep. It is a branch of animal husbandry. Sheep are raised principally for their lamb and mutton.
Pig farming is the raising and breeding of domestic pigs as livestock, and is a branch of animal husbandry. Pigs are farmed principally for food
It is the raising and breeding of Turkey commercially for meat and egg production
